# API Structure

The application uses tRPC for typesafe APIs and Next.js API routes for other endpoints.

## tRPC Structure

- `/server/routers`: tRPC router definitions organized by domain
- `/app/api/trpc/[trpc]/route.ts`: tRPC API endpoint
- `/utils/trpc`: tRPC client utilities

## Key tRPC Routers

- [server/routers/auth.ts](mdc:server/routers/auth.ts): Authentication-related procedures
- [server/routers/user.ts](mdc:server/routers/user/index.ts): User management
- [server/routers/contact.ts](mdc:server/routers/contact/index.ts): Contact management
- [server/routers/company.ts](mdc:server/routers/company.ts): Company management
- [server/routers/calendar.ts](mdc:server/routers/calendar.ts): Calendar functionality
- [server/routers/task.ts](mdc:server/routers/task.ts): Task management

## Next.js API Routes

- `/app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts`: NextAuth.js authentication
- `/app/api/upload/route.ts`: File upload handling

## Client Usage

tRPC is used in the client via React Query hooks:

```tsx
// Example usage
const { data, isLoading } = api.user.getUser.useQuery({ id: userId });
```
